1
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:07,780
Excuse me.

2
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:10,620
Hey, hey, you got a visitor.

3
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:18,460
Shut up, you.

4
00:00:19,940 --> 00:00:21,120
And what you want?

5
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:22,500
My name's John Marston.

6
00:00:23,260 --> 00:00:24,300
You wanted to speak to me.

7
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:26,740
I did?

8
00:00:27,180 --> 00:00:28,060
Apparently so.

9
00:00:29,961 --> 00:00:31,260
Why?

10
00:00:31,820 --> 00:00:34,000
I guess because we're both
in the business of the law.

11
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:45,640
You that fella from the train company?

12
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,780
No, I'm from Fort Mercer.

13
00:00:48,780 --> 00:00:49,780
Fort Mercer?

14
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:52,840
You them one of them Williamson boys.

15
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,100
Calm down.

16
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,220
Go on, shoot them, mister. Shoot them.

17
00:00:56,621 --> 00:00:58,980
Come on, what?
You getting cute with me, boy?

18
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:01,340
What's going on here?

19
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:06,320
I got me one of them Williamson boys.

20
00:01:06,980 --> 00:01:10,120
I got me one of them idiots
who give marshals a bad name.

21
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:12,640
Jonah, put your gun down.

22
00:01:19,141 --> 00:01:22,220
You must be the man from Blackwater.

23
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:23,260
Yes, sir.

24
00:01:23,780 --> 00:01:25,400
Listen, that dog ain't too bright.

25
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:27,520
But he seems loyal.

26
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:29,860
Jonah, get out of here for a minute.

27
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:33,220
Yes, sir, Mr. Johnson, sir.

28
00:01:36,321 --> 00:01:37,620
And you.

29
00:01:37,860 --> 00:01:41,480
Oh, I done seen enough of
your hide around here, friend.

30
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:45,960
I think there's some school children
down the way you can go and frighten.

31
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:48,120
Oh, hardy fucking hard.

32
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,680
Dickhead.

33
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,580
What are you doing here, Mr. Marston?

34
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:53,660
Apart from frightening my deputies.

35
00:01:56,761 --> 00:02:02,100
I'm here to capture
or kill Bill Williamson.

36
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:04,380
Okay.

37
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:05,740
Can you help me?

38
00:02:07,140 --> 00:02:08,580
He's outside my jurisdiction.

39
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:09,900
He's in the next county.

40
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:15,698
Of course, Bill Williamson
and his boys have

41
00:02:15,810 --> 00:02:17,800
tended to keep themselves
away from my town.

42
00:02:19,401 --> 00:02:21,380
So you're happy to have him out there?

43
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,920
I ain't happy, but I also ain't suicidal.

44
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:28,400
My job is to keep this town safe, not
clean up to all of these three counties.

45
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:30,360
It's hard enough around here.

46
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:34,508
You know, I hear you speak, and
suddenly I'm reminded of how some of

47
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:38,380
the people I respected most in
my life had a problem with authority.

48
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:40,480
What's wrong with you?

49
00:02:41,581 --> 00:02:44,271
Well, I'm sure you and your
fine friends have enjoyed

50
00:02:44,283 --> 00:02:48,300
spending your time running
around pursuing noble causes.

51
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,395
My cause is to keep
this town from turning

52
00:02:52,407 --> 00:02:55,100
into a living hell for
the folks who live here.

53
00:02:56,380 --> 00:02:58,080
Whole world has problems, mister.

54
00:02:58,820 --> 00:03:01,200
And I'm here doing what I can.

55
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:03,740
Why? What's happening?

56
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,840
Right now?

57
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:08,921
I got the railway, the people
who pay my salary, trying to get

58
00:03:08,933 --> 00:03:11,840
me to turn a blind eye to them
burning down settlements up there.

59
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:15,840
I got a bunch of cattle rustlers out
near Box Canyon need shutting down.

60
00:03:16,220 --> 00:03:20,080
I'm forgetting the gang that keeps murdering
homesteaders out in the backcountry.

61
00:03:20,420 --> 00:03:22,518
And I got a bunch of
hoods over in the saloon,

62
00:03:22,530 --> 00:03:24,640
drunk, threatening to
shoot up the whole town.

63
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,300
That's all I got today.

64
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,480
But it's early yet.

65
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:28,700
Give me a couple more days.

66
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:29,780
There'll be more.

67
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,260
All right.

68
00:03:31,460 --> 00:03:32,460
Tell you what.

69
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:41,700
Let's go deal with them
hoods in the saloon.

70
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:43,900
Then we'll discuss Williamson.

71
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,520
Okay, boy.

72
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,200
You're persistent, little cuss, ain't you?

73
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,220
Only when things matter.

